abstract: Etihad Airways, United Arab Emirates' national carrier, reports annual profit of $73 million, up by more than fifty percent from year earlier; warns that 'aggressive protectionism' in West threatens future growth.
lead_paragraph: Etihad Airways, the United Arab Emirates’ fast-growing national carrier, said profit rose by more than half last year but warned that “aggressive protectionist sentiment” threatened future prospects.

headline.main: Fast-Growing Etihad Airways Reports $73 Million in Profit
headline.print_headline: Fast-Growing Etihad Airways Reports $73 Million in Profit
